&lt;h2&gt;Title:                      Band 2 Occupational Therapy Assistant &lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speciality:             Neurosurgery and Health Care of the Elderly&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:                  Band 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours:                   1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; wte (37.5 hours a week)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base:                     Derriford Hospital, Plymouth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a flexible, enthusiastic and motivated individual to work in the Neurosurgery and Health Care of the Elderly team under the supervision of Occupational Therapists at Derriford Hospital. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties will include assisting in assessments of activities of daily living, on-going treatment programmes and discharge planning. Additional responsibilities include online ordering and delivery of equipment, clerical duties, telephone calls and general administration. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant will require excellent communication and time management skills and a flexible approach.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is part of a developing 7-day working rota&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
For job description or informal enquiries please contact:-&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jo Murphy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OT Team Lead Neurosurgery and Healthcare of the Elderly &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Occupational Therapy Department&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Derriford&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Plymouth PL6 8DH  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01752 432220&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
